GEICO - Mini Project : MARS models

Giovanni Fossati

PRELIMINARIES

Loading the data sets (previously saved)

datasets_list <- c("0a", "0b", 1:5)
for( i in datasets_list ) {
    dd <- readRDS(paste0("./data/data", i, "_packed.RDS"))
    assign(paste0("data", i, ".train"), dd$train)
    assign(paste0("data", i, ".test"), dd$test)
    rm(dd)
}

MARS w/ data0a

We fit data0a using R’s earth() function. The summary is shown below.

MARS0a.train <- data0a.train
MARS0a.test <-  data0a.test

# MARS wants factors
MARS0a.train$Call_Flag <- ifelse(MARS0a.train$Call_Flag, "YES", "NO") %>% factor( . )
MARS0a.test$Call_Flag  <- ifelse(MARS0a.test$Call_Flag, "YES", "NO") %>% factor( . )

MARS0a.train$MART_STATUS <- factor(MARS0a.train$MART_STATUS)
MARS0a.test$MART_STATUS <- factor(MARS0a.test$MART_STATUS)
MARS0a.train$GENDER <- factor(MARS0a.train$GENDER)
MARS0a.test$GENDER <- factor(MARS0a.test$GENDER)
MARS0a.train$CustomerSegment <- factor(MARS0a.train$CustomerSegment)
MARS0a.test$CustomerSegment <- factor(MARS0a.test$CustomerSegment)
MARS0a.model <- earth(Call_Flag ~ ., data = MARS0a.train, degree = 2, nfold = 5, ncross = 6, keepxy = TRUE)
summary(MARS0a.model)

Prediction on Test set

Setting a threshold on the response at 0.2

MARS0a.test.predict <- predict(MARS0a.model, newdata = MARS0a.test, type = "response")

MARS0a.test.performance <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = MARS0a.test.predict > MARS0a.threshold, truth = MARS0a.test$Call_Flag)
MARS0a.test.cmat <- MARS0a.test.performance$cmatrix
MARS0a.test.accuracy <- MARS0a.test.performance$accuracy

MARS0a.ROCR_pred_test <- prediction(MARS0a.test.predict, MARS0a.test$Call_Flag)
MARS0a.perf <- performance(MARS0a.ROCR_pred_test, "tpr", "fpr")
MARS0a.AUC <- as.numeric(performance(MARS0a.ROCR_pred_test, "auc")@y.values)

MARS0a.test.performance$AUC <- MARS0a.AUC
  • With a threshold at 0.2 the out-of-sample confusion matrix for this fit and train/test sets is:
MARS0a Confusion Matrix (threshold = 0.2)
NO YES
FALSE 36151 944
TRUE 1215 473

The Area Under the Curve (AUC) for this model on the test data is 0.8403, which means that our model can differentiate between a randomly selected retained and non-retained user about 84.03% of the times.

# cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 1.0, by = 0.1)
cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 0.5, by = 0.05)
t.adj <- c(-0.2, 1.7)
str_title <- paste0("ROC Curve : MARS0a")
plot(MARS0a.perf, main = str_title, lwd = 3, colorize = TRUE, print.cutoffs.at = cutoffs, text.adj = t.adj)

flag_ext <- TRUE

# perf_vs_threshold <- list()
perf_vs_threshold <- list(AUC = MARS0a.AUC)
i <- 1
for( threshold in seq(0.05, 0.4, by = 0.05)) {
    i <- i + 1
    this_model <- MARS0a.model
    this_test_data <- MARS0a.test
    this_test_predict <- predict(this_model, type = "response", newdata = this_test_data)
    
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]] <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = this_test_predict, 
                                                       threshold = threshold, 
                                                       truth = this_test_data$Call_Flag)
    names(perf_vs_threshold)[i] <- paste0("thr_", sprintf("%4.2f", threshold))
    if( i == 2 ) {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h")
    } else {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- rbind(perf_vs_threshold.table, 
                                         print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h"))
    }
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]]$AUC <- MARS0a.AUC
}
MARS0a.perf_vs_threshold <- perf_vs_threshold
MARS0a.perf_vs_threshold$table <- perf_vs_threshold.table
MARS0a.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold <- sprintf("**%.2f**", MARS0a.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold)
kable(MARS0a.perf_vs_threshold$table, digits = 3, align = "c", caption = "MARS0a Performance Measures vs. Threshold for Classification")

# cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 1.0, by = 0.1)
cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 0.5, by = 0.05)
t.adj <- c(-0.2, 1.7)
str_title <- paste0("ROC Curve : MARS2")
plot(MARS2.perf, main = str_title, lwd = 3, colorize = TRUE, print.cutoffs.at = cutoffs, text.adj = t.adj)

# perf_vs_threshold <- list()
perf_vs_threshold <- list(AUC = MARS2.AUC)
i <- 1
for( threshold in seq(0.05, 0.4, by = 0.05)) {
    i <- i + 1
    this_model <- MARS2.model
    this_test_data <- MARS2.test
    this_test_predict <- predict(this_model, type = "response", newdata = this_test_data)
    
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]] <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = this_test_predict, 
                                                       threshold = threshold, 
                                                       truth = this_test_data$Call_Flag)
    names(perf_vs_threshold)[i] <- paste0("thr_", sprintf("%4.2f", threshold))
    if( i == 2 ) {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h")
    } else {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- rbind(perf_vs_threshold.table, 
                                         print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h"))
    }
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]]$AUC <- MARS2.AUC
}
MARS2.perf_vs_threshold <- perf_vs_threshold
MARS2.perf_vs_threshold$table <- perf_vs_threshold.table
MARS2.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold <- sprintf("**%.2f**", MARS2.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold)
kable(MARS2.perf_vs_threshold$table, digits = 3, align = "c", caption = "MARS2 Performance Measures vs. Threshold for Classification")

# cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 1.0, by = 0.1)
cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 0.5, by = 0.05)
t.adj <- c(-0.2, 1.7)
str_title <- paste0("ROC Curve : MARS5")

perf_vs_threshold <- list(AUC = MARS5.AUC)
i <- 1
for( threshold in seq(0.05, 0.4, by = 0.05)) {
    i <- i + 1
    this_model <- MARS5.model
    this_test_data <- MARS5.test
    this_test_predict <- predict(this_model, type = "response", newdata = this_test_data)
    
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]] <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = this_test_predict, 
                                                       threshold = threshold, 
                                                       truth = this_test_data$Call_Flag)
    names(perf_vs_threshold)[i] <- paste0("thr_", sprintf("%4.2f", threshold))
    if( i == 2 ) {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h")
    } else {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- rbind(perf_vs_threshold.table, 
                                         print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h"))
    }
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]]$AUC <- MARS5.AUC
}
MARS5.perf_vs_threshold <- perf_vs_threshold
MARS5.perf_vs_threshold$table <- perf_vs_threshold.table
MARS5.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold <- sprintf("**%.2f**", MARS5.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold)
